          <source>Polygons in GDI+</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>A polygon is a closed shape with three or more straight sides.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, a triangle is a polygon with three sides, a rectangle is a polygon with four sides, and a pentagon is a polygon with five sides.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The following illustration shows several polygons.</source>
        </trans-unit>
